Hi, my background is Business Management but I took a Bootcamp Full Stack Java backend, JavaScript front end. Luck was on my side, I got in to a decacorn company, 3 months in and got offered 2 years contract.

I did not sign the contract because my family emphasize on finishing what I have started which is my management degree.

I intend to take another Bootcamp course in September 2022 after I finished my degree, preferably Data Science Bootcamp that focus on Computer Vision.

Will the Bootcamp neutralize the Gap year in my CV?
stories.title: Does Gap in Curriculum Vitae a Bad Thing for Software Engineer?
